# system-janitor configuration
#
# Format:        key=value (shell-sourced; bash semantics, comments with #).
# Default path:  $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/system-janitor/config
#                (typically ~/.config/system-janitor/config). Override via
#                --config <path>.
#
# All knobs here are JANITOR_* environment variables. The script applies
# the defaults shown below if a variable is unset.
#
# Section gating (KNOWN_SECTIONS = docker_prune, go_build_cache,
# tmp_gobuild_orphans, workspace_binobj, extra_cleanup, nuget_http_temp):
#
#   default-ON (run if their tooling is present):
#     docker_prune          gated by JANITOR_DOCKER_PRUNE=yes
#     go_build_cache        gated by JANITOR_GO_CLEAN=yes
#     tmp_gobuild_orphans   gated by JANITOR_TMP_GOBUILD_ORPHANS=yes
#     nuget_http_temp       gated by JANITOR_NUGET_CLEAN=yes
#
#   opt-IN (only run when a directory list is configured):
#     workspace_binobj      enabled by setting JANITOR_WORKSPACE_DIRS
#     extra_cleanup         enabled by setting JANITOR_EXTRA_CLEANUP_DIRS
#
# To run a subset of sections ad-hoc, prefer the --only <list> CLI flag
# over disabling every other JANITOR_*=no toggle individually. See the
# "Configuration reference" section of README.md for the full knob list
# and semantics.

# ── Workspace dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories scanned for .NET build artifacts
# (bin/ and obj/). The script walks up to 6 levels deep. Setting this
# value is what opts the workspace_binobj section in.
#
# JANITOR_WORKSPACE_DIRS="$HOME/code:$HOME/projects"

# ── Extra cleanup dirs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories to remove entirely on every run.
# Useful for caches that aren't covered by the built-in sections.
# Setting this value is what opts the extra_cleanup section in.
#
# Examples (uncomment selectively):
#
#   JANITOR_EXTRA_CLEANUP_DIRS="$HOME/.cache/some-tool:$HOME/.cache/playwright-old"

# ── Safety-floor dirs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Colon-separated list of directories whose inode AND total byte size
# must NOT change during the run. If any does, the run exits with code 2
# and logs user.err to syslog.
#
# Use this for paths the cleanup must NEVER touch (active session
# directories, important caches you don't trust to be left alone, etc.).
#
# JANITOR_SAFETY_FLOOR_DIRS="$HOME/.config/important-tool"

# ── Section toggles (defaults: yes if tooling is present) ─────────────
# JANITOR_DOCKER_PRUNE=yes
# JANITOR_DOCKER_VOLUMES=yes        # pass --volumes to docker system prune
# JANITOR_GO_CLEAN=yes              # gates the go_build_cache section
# JANITOR_TMP_GOBUILD_ORPHANS=yes
# JANITOR_NUGET_CLEAN=yes           # gates the nuget_http_temp section

# ── Dry-run default ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set to 1, every run behaves as if --dry-run were passed (no
# destructive ops; events still logged with status=dry_run). The
# --dry-run / -n CLI flag overrides this on a per-invocation basis.
#
# JANITOR_DRY_RUN=0

# ── Log location ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default: $XDG_STATE_HOME/janitor (~/.local/state/janitor)
#
# JANITOR_LOG_DIR="$HOME/.local/state/janitor"
